==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enthronize
<hw>En*thron"ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Enthronized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Enthronizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See
<er>Inthronize</er>.]</ety> <def>To place on a throne; hence, to induct
into office, as a bishop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There openly <qex>enthronized</qex> as the very elected king.</q>
<rj><qau>Knolles.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enthuse</ent>⟦br⟧
